1
00:00:02,036 --> 00:00:03,969
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>LET ME GET THIS STRAIGHT.</i>

2
00:00:04,038 --> 00:00:06,372
<i>YOU BUY PERSONAL ITEMS</i>
<i>FOR A SMALL AMOUNT OF MONEY,</i>

3
00:00:06,440 --> 00:00:08,507
YOU SELL THEM TO PERFECT
STRANGERS FOR A LOT MORE MONEY?

4
00:00:08,575 --> 00:00:11,710
IS AMERICA
A GREAT COUNTRY OR WHAT?

5
00:00:11,779 --> 00:00:14,045
-<i> [ Bells Jingle ]</i>
- YO, TONI.

6
00:00:14,114 --> 00:00:17,382
<i>I GOT A NICE SURPRISE</i>
<i>FOR YOU TODAY.</i>
YOU GOT A JOB?

7
00:00:17,451 --> 00:00:20,151
WHO NEEDS ONE WHEN YOU CAN
FIND RICH STUFF LIKE THIS?

8
00:00:20,220 --> 00:00:23,555
A DIGITAL CAMCORDER.
IT'S GOT LIQUID CRYSTAL DISPLAY,

9
00:00:23,624 --> 00:00:26,992
DIGITAL SOMETHING,
HEADPHONE JACK.

10
00:00:27,061 --> 00:00:29,528
NICE!

11
00:00:29,597 --> 00:00:32,697
- LOOKS LIKE
IT FELL IN THE RIVER.
- IT DID.

12
00:00:32,766 --> 00:00:35,167
I FOUND IT IN THE WASHBASIN
BELOW KOOMER FALLS.

13
00:00:35,235 --> 00:00:38,470
I FIGURE SOME MOPE
MUST HAVE BEEN MAKIN'
A HOME MOVIE AND DROPPED IT.

14
00:00:38,539 --> 00:00:40,905
GIVE YOU 20 BUCKS FOR IT.
<i>TWENTY?</i>

15
00:00:40,974 --> 00:00:43,075
I WAS LOOKING FOR
MORE LIKE A HUNDRED.

16
00:00:43,143 --> 00:00:45,877
YEAH, AND PEOPLE IN HELL
ARE LOOKIN' FOR ICE WATER.

17
00:00:45,946 --> 00:00:49,247
<i> ONE ANDREW J.</i>
<i> TAKE IT OR LEAVE IT.</i>

18
00:00:50,317 --> 00:00:52,751
YOU DRIVE A HARD BARGAIN.

19
00:00:52,820 --> 00:00:54,753
<i>[ Bells Jingle ]</i>
<i>[ Door Closes ]</i>

20
00:00:54,822 --> 00:00:56,922
WHAT'S A-- A HOME MOVIE?

21
00:00:56,990 --> 00:00:59,724
DID YOU GROW UP IN
A BASEMENT OR SOMETHING?

22
00:00:59,793 --> 00:01:03,228
- OR SOMETHING.
- YOU KNOW, MOM, DAD
AND THE KIDS...

23
00:01:03,296 --> 00:01:06,197
GO OFF ON THE GREAT
AMERICAN FAMILY VACATION...

24
00:01:06,266 --> 00:01:08,499
<i>AND RECORD IT FOR POSTERITY,</i>

25
00:01:08,568 --> 00:01:12,570
IN CASE ANYBODY
WANTS TO WATCH IT
WITHOUT A GUN TO THEIR HEAD.

26
00:01:12,639 --> 00:01:15,073
I WOULD.
I'D LOVE TO.

27
00:01:15,142 --> 00:01:18,043
<i>HOW MUCH?</i>
HUNDRED BUCKS.

28
00:01:18,111 --> 00:01:19,411
SOLD.

29
00:01:19,480 --> 00:01:24,249
LIKE I SAID,
IS AMERICA A GREAT
COUNTRY OR WHAT?

30
00:01:38,565 --> 00:01:41,099
IT'S TUESDAY THE 9th,
DAY FOUR OF OUR VACATION,

31
00:01:41,168 --> 00:01:44,069
AND TODAY WE'RE OFFICIALLY
STARTING OUR TRIP
DOWN MEMORY LANE.

32
00:01:44,137 --> 00:01:47,405
HERE ON THE BANKS
OF "KOONER"--

33
00:01:47,474 --> 00:01:50,241
WHAT IS THIS?
A STREAM OR--
IT'S A CREEK. KOOMER CREEK.

34
00:01:50,310 --> 00:01:53,745
KOOMER CREEK. YEAH.
WELL, WHATEVER IT'S CALLED,

35
00:01:53,814 --> 00:01:56,314
IT'S BEAUTIFUL.
WHAT?

36
00:01:56,383 --> 00:01:59,818
[ Both Laughing ]
[ Girl ] I THOUGHT THIS WAS
GONNA BE STUPID, BUT IT'S NEAT.

37
00:01:59,887 --> 00:02:02,353
REALLY? YOU MEAN MOM'S
NOT A COMPLETE MORON?

38
00:02:02,423 --> 00:02:05,624
WELL, NOT COMPLETE.
HA, HA, HA.

39
00:02:05,692 --> 00:02:07,893
SO THIS ALL USED TO BE
PART OF GRAMPS'S LAND?

40
00:02:07,961 --> 00:02:10,428
YEAH. THIS IS WHERE
I GREW UP.

41
00:02:10,497 --> 00:02:13,398
RIGHT OVER THERE ON THAT LOG
IS WHERE YOUR DAD
FIRST KISSED ME.

42
00:02:13,466 --> 00:02:15,801
OH, MY GOD.
LOOK. IT'S STILL THERE.

43
00:02:15,870 --> 00:02:17,803
WHAT?
LOOK.

44
00:02:17,872 --> 00:02:20,639
HERE. LET'S GET A SHOT.

45
00:02:20,708 --> 00:02:22,774
"NANCY AND TED."

46
00:02:24,077 --> 00:02:26,144
DAD TOLD ME THERE WAS
A PLACE NEAR HERE,

47
00:02:26,213 --> 00:02:28,746
LIKE, A CABIN OR SOMETHING,
YOU GUYS USED TO GO TO,
TO BE ALONE.

48
00:02:28,815 --> 00:02:30,749
HMM. IT'S AN OLD MILL.

49
00:02:30,818 --> 00:02:32,517
YEAH?
MM-HMM.

50
00:02:32,586 --> 00:02:36,254
IS THAT WHERE
I CAME FROM?
WHAT DO YOU MEAN "CAME FROM"?

51
00:02:36,323 --> 00:02:38,657
WELL, YOU SAID
THIS TRIP WAS SOMETHING
ABOUT MY HERITAGE.

52
00:02:38,726 --> 00:02:41,493
I WAS JUST WONDERING
IF YOU AND DAD GAVE--
[ Chuckles ] YEAH.

53
00:02:41,562 --> 00:02:43,962
A WHOLE NEW MEANING
TO "GRINDING THE CORN."

54
00:02:44,031 --> 00:02:46,865
LET ME TELL YOU SOMETHING,
YOUNG LADY.
HITTING TOO CLOSE TO HOME.

55
00:02:46,934 --> 00:02:50,936
UM, YOU KNOW WHAT?
I FORGOT MY FANNY PACK IN
THE CAR. I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

56
00:02:51,004 --> 00:02:53,938
OKAY. YOU KNOW, THIS PLACE
ACTUALLY DOESN'T SUCK.

57
00:02:54,007 --> 00:02:56,875
CAN'T BELIEVE YOU DIDN'T
BRING ME HERE BEFORE NOW.

58
00:03:00,047 --> 00:03:02,046
MOM, ARE YOU LISTENING TO ME?

59
00:03:02,115 --> 00:03:05,817
I'M BEING SERIOUS FOR ONCE,
AND SHE'S NOT LISTENING TO ME.

60
00:03:05,886 --> 00:03:07,452
[ Nancy ]
STOP IT! NO!

61
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:09,821
[ Girl ]
MOM, YOU OKAY?
LEAVE ME ALONE!

62
00:03:09,890 --> 00:03:11,823
- MOM?
- HELP!

63
00:03:11,892 --> 00:03:15,394
MOM, ARE YOU OKAY?
IF YOU'RE JOKING AROUND,
THIS ISN'T FUNNY.

64
00:03:18,164 --> 00:03:20,198
THIS ISN'T FUNNY.
WHERE ARE YOU?

65
00:03:20,267 --> 00:03:22,667
MOM. MOM. MOM!

66
00:03:22,736 --> 00:03:26,304
ARE YOU OKAY?
WHAT HAPPENED?
RUN. RUN.

67
00:03:26,373 --> 00:03:28,840
WHAT?
RUN. HE'S--
HE'S COMING BACK.

68
00:03:28,908 --> 00:03:30,842
- [ Man ]
HEY.
- RUN.

69
00:03:30,911 --> 00:03:33,778
HELP!
SOMEBODY HELP ME, PLEASE!
[ Screams ]

70
00:03:33,847 --> 00:03:36,347
[ Man ]
SHUT UP.
HELP!

71
00:03:36,416 --> 00:03:39,083
[ Screams ]
HELP, PLEASE!

72
00:03:39,152 --> 00:03:42,287
HELP ME!
SOMEBODY HELP US, PLEASE!

73
00:03:42,355 --> 00:03:44,356
[ Screams ]
HELP ME.

74
00:03:44,424 --> 00:03:47,426
[ Screams ]

75
00:03:48,562 --> 00:03:50,629
[ Rewinding ]

76
00:03:50,697 --> 00:03:52,998
SOMEBODY HELP US, PLEASE!

77
00:03:53,066 --> 00:03:56,901
[ Beeps ]
SOMEBODY HELP US! HELP!

78
00:03:56,970 --> 00:04:00,105
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>
<i>THERE ARE PRETENDERS AMONG US.</i>

79
00:04:00,173 --> 00:04:02,107
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>I WAS TAKEN FROM MY FAMILY.</i>

80
00:04:02,176 --> 00:04:05,744
<i>THIRTY-SIX HOURS AND HE'S</i>
<i>ALREADY DEMONSTRATING MORE</i>
<i>TALENT THAN ANY OF OUR OTHERS.</i>

81
00:04:05,813 --> 00:04:09,214
<i>HOW MANY PEOPLE DIED</i>
<i>BECAUSE OF WHAT I THOUGHT UP?</i>

82
00:04:09,282 --> 00:04:12,717
SINCE I BROKE OUT,
I'VE SPENT EVERY MOMENT
SEARCHING FOR MY PAST.

83
00:04:12,786 --> 00:04:14,986
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>HE'S A PRETENDER--</i>

84
00:04:15,055 --> 00:04:17,823
<i>A GENIUS WHO CAN BECOME</i>
<i>ANYONE THAT HE WANTS TO BE.</i>

85
00:04:17,891 --> 00:04:20,625
-<i> THE CENTRE WANTS HIM ALIVE.</i>
- PREFERABLY.

86
00:04:20,693 --> 00:04:23,628
<i>- [ Miss Parker ] HE DEFENDS</i>
<i>  THE WEAK AND ABUSED.</i>
<i>- [ Jarod ] LIFE'S A GIFT.</i>

87
00:04:35,408 --> 00:04:37,876
-<i> YOU A DOCTOR?</i>
- I AM TODAY.

88
00:04:50,991 --> 00:04:54,993
LEIGH, HONEY, MOVE OVER CLOSE
TO THE SIGN. OH, I SURE HOPE
THIS IS GONNA WORK.

89
00:04:55,062 --> 00:04:58,830
SO, IT'S MONDAY THE 8th,
DAY THREE OF OUR VACATION,

90
00:04:58,899 --> 00:05:01,633
AND WE ARE HERE AT... SLADE.

91
00:05:01,702 --> 00:05:05,937
OH, GUESS WHAT, DAD.
SHE'S GONNA LET ME DRIVE
FOR A WHILE.

92
00:05:06,006 --> 00:05:08,173
YOUR CAR.
[ Mouths Word ]

93
00:05:15,382 --> 00:05:19,584
[ Nancy ]
YEAH, NOW, THAT'S PRETTY.
BOY, DAD'S GONNA LOVE THAT.

94
00:05:19,653 --> 00:05:21,786
DO YOU HAVE TO RECORD THIS?

95
00:05:21,855 --> 00:05:23,955
[ Nancy ]
DON'T YOU HAVE
SOMETHING TO SAY?

96
00:05:24,024 --> 00:05:27,559
UM, I HAD A LITTLE ACCIDENT
IN YOUR MUSTANG.

97
00:05:27,628 --> 00:05:31,329
AND WE NEED A NEW TAILLIGHT.
BUT MOM'S GONNA CHECK AND SEE
IF THEY HAVE ONE HERE.

98
00:05:31,398 --> 00:05:33,931
AND I PROMISE
I'LL PAY FOR IT ALL.

99
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:36,301
[ Nancy ]
YEAH, RIGHT. OKAY, HERE.

100
00:05:36,370 --> 00:05:38,803
NOW, I'M GONNA GET SOME GAS.

101
00:05:38,872 --> 00:05:41,673
AND THEN I'LL CHECK AND SEE
IF THEY HAVE A NEW LIGHT.

102
00:05:42,742 --> 00:05:44,709
[ Leigh ]
"J.R.'S SERVICE STATION."

103
00:05:44,777 --> 00:05:47,545
I FEEL LIKE WE'RE IN MAYBERRY.

104
00:05:47,614 --> 00:05:50,081
ONLY IT LOOKS LIKE GOOBER'S
HAD A LOBOTOMY.

105
00:05:51,651 --> 00:05:53,752
HEY.
[ Chuckles ]

106
00:05:53,820 --> 00:05:55,753
BUT BARNEY'S GOT
A CUTE BUTT.

107
00:05:55,822 --> 00:05:58,089
[ Nancy ]
LEIGH, BEHAVE YOURSELF.

108
00:05:58,158 --> 00:06:01,359
[ Leigh ]
LIKE YOU DIDN'T NOTICE.
WHAT? I DIDN'T NOTICE.

109
00:06:01,428 --> 00:06:03,427
[ Leigh ]
YEAH, RIGHT.

110
00:06:12,138 --> 00:06:14,005
- [ Beeps ]
-<i> [ Pop ]</i>

111
00:06:24,284 --> 00:06:26,217
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>
<i>ANY NEWS FROM JAROD?</i>

112
00:06:26,286 --> 00:06:28,386
IN A MANNER OF SPEAKING.

113
00:06:28,455 --> 00:06:31,088
HE'S UP TO HIS OLD TRICKS,
BUT THIS TIME WITH A NEW TWIST.

114
00:06:31,157 --> 00:06:33,558
ONE THAT'S RIGHT UP YOUR ALLEY,
BROOTS. [ Snaps Fingers ] SIT.

115
00:06:33,627 --> 00:06:35,860
MY ALLEY. OOH.
TURN IT ON.

116
00:06:35,929 --> 00:06:37,895
[ Electronic Female Voice ]
YOU HAVE MAIL.

117
00:06:37,964 --> 00:06:41,633
WELL, HELLO, MISS PARKER. I'VE
PUT TOGETHER A LITTLE POSTCARD
FOR YOUR VIEWING PLEASURE.

118
00:06:41,701 --> 00:06:44,969
JUST CLICK AND ENJOY.

119
00:06:45,038 --> 00:06:46,971
HEY. THIS IS COOL.

120
00:06:47,040 --> 00:06:50,742
WHEN DEBBIE AND I GO TO
ROCK CITY, I CAN SEND YOU
ONE OF THESE.

121
00:06:50,811 --> 00:06:52,743
NOW, YOU'VE ALREADY MET EDNA,

122
00:06:52,812 --> 00:06:57,415
WHO DESPITE BEING LOCKED
IN AN ASYLUM FOR DECADES BY
HER LOVING HUSBAND, MR. RAINES,

123
00:06:57,484 --> 00:06:59,584
IS AN AMAZING HISTORIAN
OF THE CENTRE.

124
00:06:59,652 --> 00:07:01,886
EDNA KNOWS THINGS ABOUT
YOUR MOTHER, MISS PARKER.

125
00:07:01,955 --> 00:07:04,255
THINGS SHE WON'T TELL
TO ANYONE BUT YOU.

126
00:07:04,324 --> 00:07:06,458
<i> SHE WOULDN'T EVEN TELL ME.</i>

127
00:07:06,527 --> 00:07:08,460
EDNA WANTS TO COME HOME,
BUT SHE CAN'T.

128
00:07:08,529 --> 00:07:10,762
THERE'S AN ARMY OF SWEEPERS
OUT THERE LOOKING FOR HER.

129
00:07:10,831 --> 00:07:12,764
SHE TOLD ME HER REDEMPTION...

130
00:07:12,832 --> 00:07:15,400
WILL BE TO TELL YOU WHAT
SHE KNOWS BEFORE THEY CATCH HER.

131
00:07:15,469 --> 00:07:17,736
<i>SO YOU BETTER HURRY.</i>
<i>BE CAREFUL.</i>

132
00:07:17,805 --> 00:07:21,272
AND KNOW THAT EDNA SAID
NO MATTER WHAT HAPPENS,
SHE WANTS YOU TO KEEP DIGGING.

133
00:07:21,341 --> 00:07:24,376
THAT THE SECRET
YOUR MOTHER WANTED TO TELL YOU
WHEN YOU WERE LITTLE...

134
00:07:24,444 --> 00:07:27,245
IS BURIED OUT THERE,
AND YOU NEED TO FIND IT.

135
00:07:27,314 --> 00:07:29,247
HUH.
[ Beeps ]

136
00:07:29,316 --> 00:07:31,616
IT'S LIKE AN ELECTRONIC TRAIL
OF BREAD CRUMBS.

137
00:07:31,685 --> 00:07:35,486
THAT WE BETTER GET BUSY
FOLLOWING BEFORE SOMEONE
GOBBLES EVERYTHING UP.

138
00:07:36,489 --> 00:07:38,823
[ Coughing ]

139
00:07:38,892 --> 00:07:40,958
DAMN IT.
<i> [ Siren Blares ]</i>

140
00:07:47,601 --> 00:07:49,601
[ Coughs ]

141
00:07:53,406 --> 00:07:56,341
HAVIN' A LITTLE TROUBLE?
YOU COULD SAY THAT.

142
00:07:56,409 --> 00:07:58,976
I DON'T KNOW WHAT HAPPENED
TO IT.

143
00:07:59,045 --> 00:08:01,279
I DON'T BELIEVE I'VE SEEN YOU
AROUND HERE BEFORE.

144
00:08:01,348 --> 00:08:03,281
I'M JUST PASSING THROUGH.

145
00:08:03,350 --> 00:08:05,283
OR I WAS PASSING THROUGH.

146
00:08:05,352 --> 00:08:07,518
LOOKS LIKE I'M GONNA BE STAYING
HERE FOR
A WHILE.

147
00:08:07,587 --> 00:08:09,854
WELL, J.R.'S JUST UP
THE ROAD UP THERE.

148
00:08:09,923 --> 00:08:11,856
HOP IN.
I'LL GIVE YOU A PUSH.

149
00:08:11,925 --> 00:08:14,291
SEE IF WE CAN GET YOU
ON YOUR WAY.
[ Taps Car ]

150
00:08:15,796 --> 00:08:18,296
<i>[ Chattering On Police Radio ]</i>

151
00:08:22,035 --> 00:08:24,902
LOOKS LIKE I'M GONNA HAVE TO
ORDER THE PARTS FROM FLAGSTAFF,

152
00:08:24,971 --> 00:08:28,506
SEEING AS WE DON'T STOCK PARTS
FOR VINTAGE CARS LIKE THAT.

153
00:08:28,575 --> 00:08:30,575
BE TOMORROW BEFORE
YOU'RE UP AND RUNNIN' AGAIN.

154
00:08:30,643 --> 00:08:32,710
I CAN'T IMAGINE WHAT
MIGHT BE WRONG WITH IT.

155
00:08:32,779 --> 00:08:34,812
CORN MAN A-COMIN'.

156
00:08:34,881 --> 00:08:38,283
- THE CORN MAN?
- WELL, YOU'RE A STRANGER.

157
00:08:38,351 --> 00:08:40,652
THERE'S A CURSE
ON STRANGERS COME TO SLADE.

158
00:08:40,721 --> 00:08:43,921
<i> CURSE OF THE CORN MAN.</i>
<i> THAT'S WHY YOU'RE HAVING</i>
<i> TROUBLE WITH THE CAR.</i>

159
00:08:43,990 --> 00:08:48,026
-<i> NEWT, SHUT UP ABOUT</i>
<i> THAT OLD WIVES' TALE.</i>
- AIN'T NO WIVES' TALE.

160
00:08:48,094 --> 00:08:50,862
<i> STARTED WHEN</i>
<i> THAT STRANGER SHOWED UP AT</i>
<i> OLD MAN KOOMER'S PLACE...</i>

161
00:08:50,931 --> 00:08:53,031
BACK IN THE OLDEN DAYS.

162
00:08:53,099 --> 00:08:57,601
STRANGER CHOPPED UP THE FAMILY.
THE WHOLE FAMILY.

163
00:08:57,670 --> 00:09:01,339
<i> TINY LITTLE PIECES.</i>
<i> THEY FOUND THEM ALL</i>
<i> DOWN AT THE CORN MILL.</i>

164
00:09:01,408 --> 00:09:04,575
THE CORN MAN'S SOUL
AIN'T NEVER RESTED.

165
00:09:04,644 --> 00:09:08,212
YOU CAN SEE IT LIGHTIN'
UP THE SKY AT NIGHT.

166
00:09:08,281 --> 00:09:11,850
<i> HIS GHOST</i>
<i> STILL HAUNTS STRANGERS</i>
<i> THAT COME INTO THIS TOWN.</i>

167
00:09:11,918 --> 00:09:14,886
- I SAID SHUT UP, NEWT.
- YOU CAN TELL ME
TO SHUT UP ALL YOU WANT.

168
00:09:14,954 --> 00:09:16,887
CORN MAN'S STILL A-COMIN'.

169
00:09:19,625 --> 00:09:22,293
NOT THAT I'M PUTTIN'
ANY STOCK IN NEWT'S CURSE,

170
00:09:22,362 --> 00:09:25,964
BUT DOES SEEM LIKE
YOU'VE BEEN HAVIN' A STREAK
OF BAD LUCK LATELY.

171
00:09:26,033 --> 00:09:28,399
I HAD A COUPLE OF WOMEN
BASH RIGHT INTO ME.

172
00:09:28,468 --> 00:09:31,902
THEY SAID THEY WERE
PASSING THROUGH HERE.
MOTHER AND DAUGHTER.

173
00:09:31,971 --> 00:09:35,807
DRIVING A RED
MUSTANG CONVERTIBLE.
OH, THEY WAS PRETTY.

174
00:09:38,978 --> 00:09:41,445
THE BLONDES.

175
00:09:41,515 --> 00:09:43,982
LOOKED LIKE
THEY COULD BE SISTERS.

176
00:09:44,050 --> 00:09:47,852
THEY NEEDED A TAILLIGHT,
AS I REMEMBER, BUT I DIDN'T
HAVE ONE FOR A '65.

177
00:09:47,921 --> 00:09:51,122
<i>THEY JUST GOT SOME GAS</i>
<i>AND HEADED OUT.</i>
<i>I HAVEN'T SEEN THEM SINCE.</i>

178
00:09:51,190 --> 00:09:53,557
<i> [ Bell Dings ]</i>

179
00:09:58,231 --> 00:10:01,799
FILL HER UP, LITTLE BROTHER.
AND BE SURE AND PUT IT
ON THE DEPARTMENT'S ACCOUNT.

180
00:10:01,868 --> 00:10:05,169
YOU EVER GET TIRED OF TELLING ME
WHAT TO DO, BIG BROTHER?

181
00:10:07,674 --> 00:10:10,341
BROTHERLY LOVE,
YOU UNDERSTAND?

182
00:10:10,410 --> 00:10:13,677
<i>YOU MUST BE THE GUY</i>
<i>THE SHERIFF RADIOED IN ABOUT.</i>

183
00:10:13,746 --> 00:10:16,080
<i> WORD SURE TRAVELS FAST</i>
<i> AROUND HERE.</i>

184
00:10:16,149 --> 00:10:18,750
<i> YEAH. WELL, YOU KNOW,</i>
<i> WE LIKE TO STAY</i>
<i> ON TOP OF THINGS.</i>

185
00:10:18,819 --> 00:10:22,387
ANYTHING I CAN HELP YOU WITH?
ACTUALLY, MAYBE YOU COULD
RECOMMEND A MOTEL.

186
00:10:22,456 --> 00:10:24,789
LOOKS LIKE I'M GOING TO
BE HERE FOR A WHILE.

187
00:10:24,858 --> 00:10:27,191
WELL, CLEARWATER INN'S
THE ONLY ONE IN TOWN.

188
00:10:27,260 --> 00:10:30,428
DON'T GET MUCH BUSINESS,
EXCEPT FOR AN OCCASIONAL
TRUCKER, BUT, UH, IT'S CLEAN.

189
00:10:30,497 --> 00:10:32,530
I CAN GIVE YOU A LIFT.
AH, NO, THANKS.

190
00:10:32,598 --> 00:10:35,466
ACTUALLY, I'D-- I'D RATHER WALK.
GET TO SEE YOUR TOWN.

191
00:10:35,535 --> 00:10:37,601
DON'T BLINK.

192
00:10:37,670 --> 00:10:39,270
YOU'LL MISS IT.

193
00:10:42,609 --> 00:10:44,609
CORN MAN A-COMIN'.

194
00:11:02,962 --> 00:11:05,864
[ Beeps ]
[ Leigh ]
THE CLEARWATER INN.

195
00:11:05,932 --> 00:11:08,599
I'VE ALWAYS WANTED TO STAY
AT A ZERO-STAR RESORT.

196
00:11:08,668 --> 00:11:11,402
LEIGH, TRY AND BE NICE
FOR FIVE MINUTES.

197
00:11:12,572 --> 00:11:14,638
I AM BEING NICE.

198
00:11:21,581 --> 00:11:23,915
- [ Man ]
WELCOME TO CLEARWATER INN.
- [ Nancy ] THANK YOU.

199
00:11:23,984 --> 00:11:26,383
[ Man ]
ROOM'S ALL READY.
ROOM 14.

200
00:11:26,452 --> 00:11:29,520
[ Nancy ]
ROOM 14 IT IS.
[ Man ] PRESIDENTIAL SUITE.

201
00:11:29,589 --> 00:11:32,490
WHAT PRESIDENT STAYED HERE?
MILLARD FILLMORE?

202
00:11:32,558 --> 00:11:34,558
WELL, ACTUALLY,
I JUST CALL IT THAT...

203
00:11:34,627 --> 00:11:38,396
SO I CAN CHARGE MORE
TO SMART-MOUTHED KIDS
AND THEIR MOTHERS.

204
00:11:38,464 --> 00:11:40,865
[ Leigh Chuckles ]
CLEVER.

205
00:11:40,934 --> 00:11:43,868
I'M SURE IT'LL BE JUST FINE.

206
00:11:43,937 --> 00:11:46,770
THANK YOU, RAYMOND.
COME ON. LET'S GO.

207
00:11:50,510 --> 00:11:52,076
[ Beeps ]

208
00:11:58,384 --> 00:12:00,518
HELLO.

209
00:12:00,587 --> 00:12:03,154
I'D LIKE TO
RENT A ROOM, PLEASE.

210
00:12:03,223 --> 00:12:07,625
FILL THIS OUT. BE SURE
AND PUT DOWN THE MAKE
AND MODEL OF YOUR CAR.

211
00:12:07,694 --> 00:12:10,928
ACTUALLY, I'M GOING TO
NEED A RENTAL.
UH, TWO BLOCKS THAT WAY.

212
00:12:10,997 --> 00:12:13,598
AND GOOD LUCK
WITH WHAT YOU GET.
WELL, IT DOESN'T MATTER.

213
00:12:13,667 --> 00:12:16,568
JUST WANT TO DRIVE AROUND.
IT'S BEAUTIFUL HERE.

214
00:12:16,636 --> 00:12:18,903
[ Chuckles ]
WELL, THAT'S IN THE EYES
OF THE BEHOLDER.

215
00:12:18,972 --> 00:12:21,305
SOME FRIENDS OF MINE
SEEMED TO HAVE THOUGHT SO.

216
00:12:21,374 --> 00:12:25,242
AS A MATTER OF FACT, I THINK
THEY STAYED HERE A COUPLE OF
DAYS AGO. A MOTHER AND DAUGHTER.

217
00:12:25,312 --> 00:12:27,545
BEAUTIFUL, BLONDE.

218
00:12:28,548 --> 00:12:30,949
MMM. DON'T REMEMBER 'EM.

219
00:12:32,519 --> 00:12:34,952
I HEAR YOU ONLY GET
THE OCCASIONAL TRUCKER
THROUGH HERE.

220
00:12:35,021 --> 00:12:38,155
SURELY YOU REMEMBER
TWO BEAUTIFUL WOMEN
IN A RED CONVERTIBLE.

221
00:12:38,224 --> 00:12:41,993
HMM. WELL,
YOU'D THINK I WOULD.

222
00:12:42,062 --> 00:12:44,329
BUT I DON'T,
BECAUSE THEY WEREN'T HERE.

223
00:12:51,537 --> 00:12:53,538
HERE WE GO.

224
00:12:54,840 --> 00:12:57,241
THINK WE'LL PUT YOU
IN ROOM NUMBER FIVE.

225
00:12:57,310 --> 00:12:59,510
<i> I'LL TAKE NUMBER 14,</i>
<i> PLEASE.</i>

226
00:12:59,579 --> 00:13:01,512
IT'S MY FAVORITE NUMBER.

227
00:13:01,581 --> 00:13:03,614
SURE.

228
00:13:06,686 --> 00:13:08,619
FOURTEEN IT IS THEN.

229
00:13:30,777 --> 00:13:33,410
YEAH, THERE'S SOMEONE HERE
ASKING ABOUT 'EM.

230
00:13:33,479 --> 00:13:35,880
EVEN KNEW WHAT ROOM
THEY WERE IN.

231
00:13:37,183 --> 00:13:39,349
MOM. DO YOU BELIEVE
IN GHOSTS?

232
00:13:39,418 --> 00:13:42,386
[ Nancy ] GHOSTS?
YEAH. YOU KNOW,
THE SOULS OF THE DEAD.

233
00:13:42,455 --> 00:13:44,755
<i>THEY CAN COME BACK</i>
<i>TO HAUNT THE LIVING.</i>

234
00:13:44,824 --> 00:13:47,725
I DON'T KNOW, HONEY.
I NEVER REALLY GAVE IT
THAT MUCH THOUGHT.

235
00:13:47,794 --> 00:13:49,861
[ Leigh ]
THEN HOW DO YOU EXPLAIN
THOSE FLASHES?

236
00:13:49,929 --> 00:13:51,862
[ Nancy ]
IT'S CALLED HEAT LIGHTNING.

237
00:13:51,931 --> 00:13:56,834
- AND IT'S BEEN HAPPENING
AROUND HERE FOR A LONG TIME.
- WHATEVER IT IS, IT'S FREAKY.

238
00:13:56,903 --> 00:14:00,137
LIKE THAT STORY
THAT GUY WAS TELLING ME
BACK AT THE GAS STATION.

239
00:14:00,206 --> 00:14:02,172
YOU KNOW, THE ONE
THAT GAVE ME THIS.

240
00:14:02,241 --> 00:14:04,375
<i> HE WAS TELLING ME</i>
<i> ABOUT THE CURSE.</i>

241
00:14:04,444 --> 00:14:06,810
ALL STRANGERS ARE CURSED.
HMM.

242
00:14:06,879 --> 00:14:11,181
IT ALL STARTED BACK WHEN SOME
CORN MAN HACKED UP A FAMILY
OUT BY GRANDPA'S OLD RANCH.

243
00:14:11,250 --> 00:14:14,585
<i>[ Nancy ] HONEY, THAT'S JUST</i>
<i>AN OLD TALE THAT PEOPLE</i>
<i>HAVE BEEN TELLING FOR YEARS.</i>

244
00:14:14,654 --> 00:14:17,221
IT'S RIDICULOUS.

245
00:14:17,290 --> 00:14:20,257
I HOPE SO.
IT IS.

246
00:14:20,326 --> 00:14:22,259
OKAY.

247
00:14:22,328 --> 00:14:26,597
WAIT. HOW DO YOU
TURN THIS OFF AGAIN?
LITTLE RED BUTTON.

248
00:14:28,367 --> 00:14:30,300
MOM.
WHAT?

249
00:14:30,369 --> 00:14:33,137
MOM, THERE'S
SOMEBODY OUT THERE.
WHAT? WHERE?

250
00:14:33,206 --> 00:14:36,040
BY THE TREE.
HE WAS STANDING--
HE'S STARING AT ME.

251
00:14:36,108 --> 00:14:38,743
<i>[ Nancy ]</i>
<i>OKAY.</i>

252
00:14:38,811 --> 00:14:40,911
<i> LOOK.</i>

253
00:14:41,914 --> 00:14:43,914
<i>[ Nancy ]</i>
<i>I DON'T SEE ANYONE.</i>

254
00:14:46,086 --> 00:14:48,352
HE WAS RIGHT THERE
BY THE TREE.
I SWEAR.

255
00:14:48,421 --> 00:14:50,721
<i>[ Nancy ]</i>
<i>IF THERE WAS SOMEONE THERE,</i>
<i>THEY'RE NOT THERE NOW.</i>

256
00:14:50,790 --> 00:14:54,292
HE WARNED US
WE'D BE IN DANGER.
MAYBE HE WAS RIGHT.

257
00:14:54,360 --> 00:14:56,293
MAYBE THE CORN MAN'S
COMING, MOM.

258
00:14:56,362 --> 00:14:57,929
<i>[ Nancy ]</i>
<i>THAT'S NOT HAPPENING.</i>

259
00:14:59,732 --> 00:15:01,732
GO TO BED.

260
00:15:07,039 --> 00:15:09,040
HOW DO I
TURN THIS OFF AGAIN?

261
00:15:13,078 --> 00:15:15,079
<i>[ Owl Hooting ]</i>

262
00:15:35,301 --> 00:15:37,368
<i>[ Young Sydney's Voice ]</i>
<i>JAROD, A 15-YEAR-OLD GIRL...</i>

263
00:15:37,436 --> 00:15:39,970
<i>IS FOUND BRUTALLY MURDERED</i>
<i>IN HER BEDROOM.</i>

264
00:15:40,039 --> 00:15:43,140
PART OF AN UPPER-CLASS
COMMUNITY IN A SMALL TOWN.

265
00:15:43,208 --> 00:15:46,443
WE DON'T KNOW WHAT HAPPENED
BETWEEN THE TIME
SHE LEFT HER FRIENDS...

266
00:15:46,512 --> 00:15:49,213
<i>AND WHEN SHE WAS MURDERED.</i>
WHAT IS IT
YOU WANT ME TO DO, SYDNEY?

267
00:15:49,282 --> 00:15:51,915
<i>TAKE THE EVIDENCE.</i>
<i>USE YOUR SKILLS AS A PRETENDER.</i>

268
00:15:51,985 --> 00:15:56,120
<i>BECOME THE VICTIM.</i>
<i>DO WHAT SHE DID.</i>
<i>FEEL WHAT SHE FELT.</i>

269
00:15:59,158 --> 00:16:01,525
<i>[ Leigh ]</i>
<i>IT'S TUESDAY THE 9th,</i>
<i>DAY FOUR OF OUR VACATION,</i>

270
00:16:01,593 --> 00:16:05,562
<i>AND TODAY WE'RE OFFICIALLY</i>
<i>STARTING OUR TRIP</i>
<i>DOWN MEMORY LANE.</i>

271
00:16:05,631 --> 00:16:09,967
<i>HERE ON THE BANKS OF "KOONER"--</i>
<i>WHAT IS THIS?</i>
<i>A STREAM OR--</i>

272
00:16:10,035 --> 00:16:13,069
-<i> [ Nancy's Voice ]</i>
<i>  IT'S A CREEK. KOOMER CREEK.</i>
-<i> [ Leigh ] KOOMER CREEK.</i>

273
00:16:13,138 --> 00:16:16,006
<i>YEAH. WELL, WHATEVER</i>
<i>IT'S CALLED, IT'S BEAUTIFUL.</i>

274
00:16:16,074 --> 00:16:18,008
<i>[ Nancy ]</i>
<i>THIS IS WHERE I GREW UP.</i>

275
00:16:18,077 --> 00:16:22,379
<i>[ Leigh ]</i>
<i>YOU KNOW, THIS PLACE</i>
<i>ACTUALLY DOESN'T SUCK.</i>

276
00:16:22,448 --> 00:16:25,449
<i>CAN'T BELIEVE YOU DIDN'T</i>
<i>BRING ME HERE BEFORE NOW.</i>
<i> [ Nancy ] STOP IT!</i>

277
00:16:25,517 --> 00:16:27,785
<i> NO!</i>
<i>MOM?</i>

278
00:16:27,853 --> 00:16:29,853
<i> LEAVE ME ALONE!</i>
<i>YOU OKAY? MOM?</i>

279
00:16:29,922 --> 00:16:32,889
-<i> HELP!</i>
-<i> MOM, ARE YOU OKAY?</i>

280
00:16:32,958 --> 00:16:35,726
<i>MOM, IF YOU'RE KIDDING AROUND,</i>
<i>THIS ISN'T FUNNY.</i>
<i>WHERE ARE YOU?</i>

281
00:16:37,062 --> 00:16:38,529
<i>MOM!</i>

282
00:16:41,433 --> 00:16:43,434
MOM.

283
00:17:00,953 --> 00:17:03,020
<i>[ Leigh ]</i>
<i>MOM. MOM.</i>

284
00:17:03,088 --> 00:17:04,755
ARE YOU OKAY?
WHAT HAPPENED?

285
00:17:06,325 --> 00:17:08,492
RUN. HE'S--
HE'S COMING BACK.

286
00:17:08,561 --> 00:17:10,227
<i> RUN.</i>

287
00:17:10,296 --> 00:17:13,130
<i> I CAN'T SEE IT, SYDNEY.</i>
<i> I CAN'T FIGURE IT OUT.</i>

288
00:17:13,199 --> 00:17:16,834
<i>YOU HAVE TO FIGURE IT OUT.</i>
<i>THE FAMILY IS COUNTING ON YOU.</i>

289
00:17:19,972 --> 00:17:23,206
[ Screams ]

290
00:17:23,275 --> 00:17:25,742
SOMEBODY HELP US, PLEASE!

291
00:17:43,295 --> 00:17:46,030
<i>[ Newt's Voice ]</i>
<i>CORN MAN A-COMIN'.</i>
<i>[ Echoing ]</i>

292
00:17:52,838 --> 00:17:55,405
WELL, MISTER,
YOU'RE GOOD TO GO.

293
00:17:55,474 --> 00:17:57,407
FUNNY THING,
PARTS SHOP SAID...

294
00:17:57,476 --> 00:18:00,144
THEY NEVER HEARD
OF THIS HAPPENING
WITH THIS MODEL BEFORE.

295
00:18:00,212 --> 00:18:02,179
WELL, THAT IS FUNNY.

296
00:18:02,248 --> 00:18:04,381
<i> NOT IF YOU'RE A STRANGER</i>
<i> IT AIN'T.</i>

297
00:18:04,450 --> 00:18:06,983
IT'S THE CURSE.

298
00:18:07,052 --> 00:18:10,187
THAT'S WHY I WENT
AND MADE YOU THIS HERE
CORN MAN TO KEEP YOU SAFE.

299
00:18:10,255 --> 00:18:14,024
IF YOU'RE GONNA
STAY AROUND HERE,
YOU'RE GONNA NEED IT.

300
00:18:14,093 --> 00:18:16,327
THANKS.

301
00:18:16,395 --> 00:18:18,596
I THINK.
<i> [ Bell Dings ]</i>

302
00:18:18,664 --> 00:18:20,664
<i> [ Man On Police Radio,</i>
<i> Indistinct ]</i>

303
00:18:22,401 --> 00:18:26,103
WELL, I SEE KENT'S GOT YOU
ALL FIXED UP THERE,

304
00:18:26,172 --> 00:18:27,704
<i> MR., UH--</i>

305
00:18:27,773 --> 00:18:30,174
YOU KNOW, I'M NOT SURE
I GOT YOUR NAME.

306
00:18:30,242 --> 00:18:32,509
I'M NOT SURE
I GAVE YOU MY NAME.

307
00:18:32,578 --> 00:18:35,178
GUESS YOU'LL BE
ON YOUR WAY THEN.

308
00:18:35,247 --> 00:18:38,715
WHO KNOWS? MAYBE I'LL STICK
AROUND. I'M GROWING KIND OF
ATTACHED TO THE PLACE.

309
00:18:38,785 --> 00:18:41,251
<i> YOU DON'T GOT A JOB</i>
<i> OR A HOME TO GO BACK TO?</i>

310
00:18:41,320 --> 00:18:44,121
I'M SORT OF IN BETWEEN
BOTH RIGHT NOW.

311
00:18:44,190 --> 00:18:46,489
WELL, I'D ADVISE YOU GET
ONE OR THE OTHER.

312
00:18:46,558 --> 00:18:48,558
IDLE HANDS ARE
THE DEVIL'S PLAYTHINGS.

313
00:18:50,229 --> 00:18:52,229
I DON'T PLAN TO BE IDLE.

314
00:18:57,436 --> 00:18:59,436
I'M NOT TOO FOND
OF STRANGERS.

315
00:19:00,606 --> 00:19:03,440
<i> I HOPE THE CORN MAN</i>
<i> DON'T GET HIM.</i>

316
00:19:07,279 --> 00:19:09,280
ANY LUCK FINDING EDNA?
<i>[ Broots Clears Throat ]</i>

317
00:19:09,348 --> 00:19:13,217
I'VE ENHANCED THIS PHOTO FROM
JAROD'S E-MAIL. THERE'S NO ONE
WE RECOGNIZE IN THE CROWD,

318
00:19:13,286 --> 00:19:17,121
BUT FROM THE SIGNAGE AND
LICENSE PLATES, IT LOOKS LIKE
A STREET SCENE IN NEW YORK CITY.

319
00:19:17,189 --> 00:19:18,922
SOMEWHERE IN HARLEM.
<i> [ Broots ]</i>
<i> HMM.</i>

320
00:19:18,991 --> 00:19:22,626
-<i> [ Beeps ]</i>
- [ Jarod's Voice ] EDNA WANTS
TO COME HOME, BUT SHE CAN'T.

321
00:19:22,695 --> 00:19:25,128
THERE'S AN ARMY OF SWEEPERS
OUT THERE LOOKING FOR HER.

322
00:19:25,197 --> 00:19:27,131
SHE TOLD ME HER REDEMPTION...

323
00:19:27,199 --> 00:19:29,933
WILL BE TO TELL YOU WHAT
SHE KNOWS BEFORE THEY CATCH HER.

324
00:19:30,002 --> 00:19:31,601
<i> SO YOU BETTER HURRY.</i>
HMM.

325
00:19:31,670 --> 00:19:34,605
HOME. REDEMPTION.

326
00:19:36,809 --> 00:19:39,109
OF COURSE.
ONE OF MY MOTHER'S
FAVORITE CHARITIES...

327
00:19:39,178 --> 00:19:42,278
<i> WAS A HALFWAY HOUSE</i>
<i> IN HARLEM CALLED</i>
<i> REDEMPTION HOME.</i>

328
00:19:43,982 --> 00:19:46,617
<i>[ Broots ]</i>
<i>JAROD'S TELLING YOU</i>
<i>THAT'S WHERE YOU CAN FIND EDNA.</i>

329
00:20:03,602 --> 00:20:06,569
<i> [ Doorbell Rings ]</i>

330
00:20:10,743 --> 00:20:12,876
MR. WRIGHT?
MM-HMM.

331
00:20:14,580 --> 00:20:17,581
I HAVE TO TALK TO YOU
ABOUT YOUR WIFE
AND YOUR DAUGHTER.

332
00:20:17,650 --> 00:20:21,952
THERE'S BEEN SOME TROUBLE.
TROUBLE? WHAT DO YOU MEAN?
I-- I JUST SPOKE WITH THEM.

333
00:20:22,021 --> 00:20:25,989
- WHEN?
- THIS MORNING.

334
00:20:26,058 --> 00:20:29,659
THEY SAID THEY WERE FINE.
WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?

335
00:20:32,698 --> 00:20:34,665
WE'VE HAD
A MINOR CAR ACCIDENT.

336
00:20:37,002 --> 00:20:39,369
WELL, THAT'S STRANGE.
NANCY DIDN'T MENTION
ANYTHING ABOUT IT.

337
00:20:39,438 --> 00:20:41,304
THAT IS STRANGE.

338
00:20:41,373 --> 00:20:43,873
<i>THAT CAR MUST MEAN</i>
<i>A LOT TO YOU.</i>

339
00:20:43,942 --> 00:20:47,477
ACTUALLY,
IT WAS YOUR DAUGHTER
WHO WAS DRIVING. LEIGH.

340
00:20:47,546 --> 00:20:49,880
<i>SHE BACKED INTO ME.</i>

341
00:20:49,949 --> 00:20:52,883
<i>UH, YOUR WIFE GAVE ME</i>
<i>THE NAME AND NUMBER</i>
<i>OF YOUR INSURANCE COMPANY,</i>

342
00:20:52,952 --> 00:20:55,185
BUT I-- I SEEM TO HAVE
MISPLACED IT.

343
00:20:55,253 --> 00:20:57,221
IS YOUR WIFE
EXPECTED HOME SOON?

344
00:20:57,290 --> 00:21:01,424
NO. THEY'RE BOTH STILL OUT OF
TOWN. LOOK. ALL MY INSURANCE IS
HANDLED THROUGH WESTERN MUTUAL.

345
00:21:01,493 --> 00:21:03,660
BUT, YOU KNOW, I PREFER
TO HANDLE THIS MYSELF.

346
00:21:03,729 --> 00:21:07,431
SO WHY DON'T YOU GET
AN ESTIMATE, AND I'LL SEND YOU
A CHECK FOR THE FULL AMOUNT.

347
00:21:07,500 --> 00:21:09,699
YES, BUT I WOULD NOT-- UH--

348
00:21:11,603 --> 00:21:13,603
I'LL BE IN TOUCH.

349
00:21:18,477 --> 00:21:22,046
SOMEBODY WAS HERE.
HE WAS ASKING ABOUT THEM.

350
00:21:22,114 --> 00:21:24,481
TALL GUY. DARK HAIR.

351
00:21:31,857 --> 00:21:33,890
[ Electronic Twittering, Beeps ]

352
00:22:09,327 --> 00:22:12,329
<i>[ Horns Honking ]</i>

353
00:22:12,398 --> 00:22:14,431
<i>[ Broots's Voice ]</i>
<i>EDNA RAINES IS IN THIS BUILDING.</i>

354
00:22:14,499 --> 00:22:16,933
HERE IN ROOM 24.

355
00:22:17,002 --> 00:22:21,271
BUT THE GUY SAID THAT I WAS
THE SECOND PERSON TO LOOK
FOR HER IN THE LAST HALF HOUR.

356
00:22:26,679 --> 00:22:30,147
-<i> [ Sydney ] RAINES.</i>
- [ Raines ] WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU DOING HERE?

357
00:22:30,216 --> 00:22:32,683
WHAT THE HELL
ARE<i> YOU</i> DOING HERE?

358
00:22:32,751 --> 00:22:35,018
SHE WAS MY WIFE.

359
00:22:35,087 --> 00:22:39,656
- WAS?
- [ Sydney ]
EDNA RAINES IS DEAD.

360
00:22:39,725 --> 00:22:42,625
AN OVERDOSE.

361
00:22:46,065 --> 00:22:47,998
HOW CONVENIENT.

362
00:22:51,503 --> 00:22:54,170
I CAN ONLY ASSUME
SHE COULDN'T
FACE THE WORLD ANY LONGER.

363
00:22:54,239 --> 00:22:56,807
WITH YOU IN IT,
WHO COULD BLAME HER?

364
00:22:56,875 --> 00:22:59,109
I'LL MISS HER SO MUCH.

365
00:22:59,178 --> 00:23:02,346
IS THAT WHY YOU KEPT HER
LOCKED UP FOR 30 YEARS?

366
00:23:03,649 --> 00:23:05,648
THAT WAS TO PROTECT HER.

367
00:23:05,717 --> 00:23:10,120
<i> YOU NEVER PROTECTED ANYONE</i>
<i> BUT YOURSELF, RAINES.</i>

368
00:23:13,124 --> 00:23:15,358
YOU CAN BURY HER
AGAIN, RAINES.

369
00:23:15,427 --> 00:23:19,096
<i> ALONG WITH ALL THE SECRETS</i>
<i> SHE DIED FOR.</i>

370
00:23:30,642 --> 00:23:32,575
SHERIFF.
YEAH.

371
00:23:32,644 --> 00:23:35,312
WE NEED TO TALK.
<i> [ Phone Rings ]</i>

372
00:23:35,381 --> 00:23:38,481
UH, JUST A SECOND
THERE, SIR.
YEAH. SHERIFF'S OFFICE.

373
00:23:38,550 --> 00:23:41,818
<i> WHAT? NO.</i>
<i> YOUR BROTHER'S NOT HERE.</i>

374
00:23:41,887 --> 00:23:44,888
<i> YEAH. HE-- HE IS</i>
<i> THE DEPUTY, KENT.</i>
<i> HE'S ON PATROL.</i>

375
00:23:44,957 --> 00:23:48,425
<i>YEAH. I'LL TELL HIM</i>
<i>TO CALL YOU WHEN HE GETS BACK.</i>

376
00:23:48,494 --> 00:23:50,760
ALL RIGHT. OKAY.

377
00:23:50,829 --> 00:23:53,396
SORRY ABOUT THAT. WHAT, UH--
WHAT'S THE PROBLEM NOW?

378
00:23:53,465 --> 00:23:56,066
I FOUND SOMETHING, AND I WANT
TO SHOW YOU. I WAS--
<i> [ Phone Rings ]</i>

379
00:23:56,134 --> 00:23:59,269
DAMN IT.
SHERIFF'S OFFICE.

380
00:24:02,674 --> 00:24:06,176
YEAH. UH, LISTEN.
I CAN'T TALK RIGHT NOW. UM--

381
00:24:07,412 --> 00:24:09,579
<i> I UNDERSTAND. I--</i>

382
00:24:09,648 --> 00:24:12,515
<i>I'LL GET RIGHT BACK WITH YOU.</i>
<i>SOON. ALL RIGHT? YEAH.</i>

383
00:24:19,592 --> 00:24:23,026
JUST STAY THERE.
<i>[ Door Closes ]</i>

384
00:24:31,303 --> 00:24:33,236
<i>[ Engine Starts ]</i>

385
00:24:50,288 --> 00:24:52,889
<i>[ Birds Chirping ]</i>

386
00:26:19,678 --> 00:26:21,644
<i>[ Sheriff's Voice ]</i>
<i>WAKE UP.</i>

387
00:26:21,713 --> 00:26:23,446
I SAID WAKE UP!

388
00:26:23,515 --> 00:26:25,248
START TALKIN'.

389
00:26:25,317 --> 00:26:28,118
TALKIN' ABOUT WHAT?

390
00:26:28,187 --> 00:26:30,153
EVERYTHING YOU KNOW
ABOUT NANCY AND LEIGH.

391
00:26:30,222 --> 00:26:32,789
FROM THE BEGINNING.

392
00:26:32,858 --> 00:26:34,824
I KNOW THEY DISAPPEARED
FOUR DAYS AGO.

393
00:26:34,893 --> 00:26:38,895
AND I KNOW THAT MR. WRIGHT HERE
HAS TAKEN OUT A RATHER LARGE
INSURANCE POLICY ON THEM.

394
00:26:38,963 --> 00:26:40,897
HEY. WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU SAYIN'?

395
00:26:40,966 --> 00:26:43,133
I'M SAYIN' THAT
YOU AND THE SHERIFF HERE...

396
00:26:43,202 --> 00:26:45,401
HAVE CONSPIRED TO MURDER
YOUR WIFE AND YOUR DAUGHTER...

397
00:26:45,470 --> 00:26:47,270
SO YOU COULD COLLECT
INSURANCE MONEY.
MURDER?

398
00:26:47,339 --> 00:26:50,140
- PAL, WE'RE TRYING
TO SAVE THEM.
-<i> THAT WHY YOU TRIED TO KILL ME?</i>

399
00:26:50,209 --> 00:26:53,075
- KILL YA? WE FOUND YOU.
-<i> YOU KIDNAPPED</i>
<i> MY WIFE AND DAUGHTER.</i>

400
00:26:53,144 --> 00:26:55,478
- YOU'RE GONNA
TELL US WHERE THEY ARE.
- KIDNAPPED?

401
00:26:55,547 --> 00:26:57,814
<i> I DIDN'T KIDNAP THEM.</i>
<i> I'M HERE TO FIND THEM.</i>

402
00:26:57,883 --> 00:27:02,018
LOOK. THERE'S A CAMCORDER OVER
THERE. THERE'S A TAPE IN IT.
IT WILL EXPLAIN EVERYTHING.

403
00:27:02,087 --> 00:27:04,087
<i> [ Beeps ]</i>

404
00:27:04,155 --> 00:27:06,990
ARE YOU OKAY?
WHAT HAPPENED?
RUN. RUN.

405
00:27:07,058 --> 00:27:10,326
WHAT?
RUN. HE'S--
HE'S COMING BACK.

406
00:27:10,395 --> 00:27:12,428
RUN.
HELP!

407
00:27:12,498 --> 00:27:14,764
[ Man ] HEY.
HELP ME, PLEASE!
[ Screams ]

408
00:27:14,833 --> 00:27:18,134
HELP.
[ Screams ]

409
00:27:18,203 --> 00:27:21,671
<i> HELP!</i>
<i> SOMEBODY HELP US, PLEASE!</i>

410
00:27:21,740 --> 00:27:24,641
<i> [ Ted ]</i>
<i> OH, MY GOD.</i>

411
00:27:24,709 --> 00:27:27,644
WHO THE HELL ARE YOU?

412
00:27:27,713 --> 00:27:32,215
I WAS ON VACATION WHEN
THIS SORT OF FELL INTO MY LAP.

413
00:27:34,920 --> 00:27:37,821
- JAROD WILSON, U.S. MARSHALS.
-<i> [ Ted ]</i>
<i>  A FED.</i>

414
00:27:37,889 --> 00:27:41,858
- DAMN IT, FRANK. HE FINDS OUT,
HE'S GONNA KILL THEM.
- WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

415
00:27:47,132 --> 00:27:49,533
FOUR DAYS AGO
I GOT A CALL. A MAN.

416
00:27:49,601 --> 00:27:52,202
<i>HE SAID IF I WANTED TO SEE</i>
<i>MY WIFE AND DAUGHTER AGAIN...</i>

417
00:27:52,270 --> 00:27:54,938
TO GET $500,000
BY TONIGHT...

418
00:27:55,007 --> 00:27:57,073
AND NOT TO CONTACT
THE AUTHORITIES.

419
00:27:57,142 --> 00:28:00,676
<i>TED GOT A HOLD OF ME</i>
<i>AND MADE ME PROMISE I WOULDN'T</i>
<i>BRING IN ANY OUTSIDE HELP.</i>

420
00:28:00,745 --> 00:28:03,847
<i>WE'VE BEEN, UH, FRIENDS</i>
<i>SINCE HIGH SCHOOL--</i>
<i>AND RAYMOND HERE.</i>

421
00:28:03,915 --> 00:28:07,817
<i> THEN YOU STARTED SNIFFIN'</i>
<i> AROUND, AND WE FIGURED</i>
<i> YOU WERE INVOLVED.</i>

422
00:28:07,886 --> 00:28:11,421
DO YOU THINK
IT'S SOMEONE LOCAL?

423
00:28:11,489 --> 00:28:16,292
WELL, A LOT OF LOCAL PEOPLE
ARE AWARE OF TED'S FINANCIAL
SUCCESS AND HIS FAMILY.

424
00:28:16,361 --> 00:28:18,862
<i>TO TELL YOU THE TRUTH,</i>
<i>WE DON'T HAVE MUCH TO GO ON.</i>

425
00:28:18,931 --> 00:28:20,931
<i>AND EVEN LESS TIME.</i>

426
00:28:29,107 --> 00:28:31,708
<i>[ Sydney's Voice ]</i>
<i>I WAS EDNA RAINES'S THERAPIST.</i>

427
00:28:31,776 --> 00:28:35,278
I CAN ASSURE YOU THAT
SHE WOULDN'T HAVE TAKEN HER OWN
LIFE-- AT LEAST NOT WILLINGLY.

428
00:28:35,347 --> 00:28:37,814
EDNA KNEW SHE WAS IN DANGER.

429
00:28:37,883 --> 00:28:40,516
THAT'S WHY JAROD WAS
SO CRYPTIC ABOUT HER LOCATION.

430
00:28:40,585 --> 00:28:42,918
- [ Beeps ]
-<i> [ Jarod's Voice ]</i>
<i> BE CAREFUL.</i>

431
00:28:42,987 --> 00:28:46,189
AND KNOW THAT EDNA SAID
NO MATTER WHAT HAPPENS,
SHE WANTS YOU TO KEEP DIGGING.

432
00:28:46,257 --> 00:28:49,126
THAT THE SECRET
YOUR MOTHER WANTED TO TELL YOU
WHEN YOU WERE LITTLE...

433
00:28:49,194 --> 00:28:52,262
<i> IS BURIED OUT THERE,</i>
<i> AND YOU NEED TO FIND IT.</i>

434
00:28:52,330 --> 00:28:55,264
BURIED? BUT WHERE?

435
00:28:55,333 --> 00:28:58,634
<i>WHO'S THE MOST ADEPT</i>
<i>AT BURYING THINGS AROUND HERE?</i>

436
00:28:58,703 --> 00:29:01,037
[ Gulps ]
MR. RAINES.

437
00:29:01,106 --> 00:29:03,473
<i> [ Printer Whirring ]</i>

438
00:29:11,282 --> 00:29:13,383
GOT THE CASH.

439
00:29:13,451 --> 00:29:16,152
EVERYTHING'S READY TO GO.

440
00:29:16,221 --> 00:29:19,089
HE SHOULD'VE CALLED
BY NOW TO TELL ME
WHERE TO DROP THE MONEY.

441
00:29:19,157 --> 00:29:21,657
HE'S GOING TO CALL,
MR. WRIGHT.
JUST BE PATIENT.

442
00:29:21,726 --> 00:29:24,494
I DON'T WANT TO BE PATIENT.
I WANT MY FAMILY BACK.

443
00:29:24,563 --> 00:29:27,330
TED, HE'S ON OUR SIDE.

444
00:29:27,399 --> 00:29:29,399
<i> [ Cell Phone Rings ]</i>

445
00:29:29,468 --> 00:29:32,335
KEEP HIM ON THE LINE
AS LONG AS POSSIBLE.

446
00:29:32,404 --> 00:29:34,337
TELL HIM YOU DEMAND
TO SPEAK TO NANCY--

447
00:29:34,406 --> 00:29:37,273
THAT YOU WON'T MAKE
A DELIVERY UNTIL YOU KNOW
THAT YOUR WIFE IS SAFE.

448
00:29:37,342 --> 00:29:40,210
-<i> [ Ringing Continues ]</i>
- [ Computer Beeps ]

449
00:29:41,513 --> 00:29:43,746
[ Beeps ]
THIS IS WRIGHT.

450
00:29:43,815 --> 00:29:45,515
[ Beeps ]

451
00:29:45,584 --> 00:29:49,252
<i>[ Man ] PUT THE MONEY</i>
<i>IN A DUFFEL BAG. AT MIDNIGHT,</i>
<i>YOU, AND YOU ALONE--</i>

452
00:29:49,321 --> 00:29:54,090
[ Distorted Voice ] WILL TAKE IT
AND LEAVE IT IN THE TRASH BIN AT
THE BRIDGE ON LONG TUNNEL ROAD.

453
00:29:54,158 --> 00:29:58,194
- I WANT TO TALK TO MY WIFE.
-<i> [ Man ] YOU'RE NOT IN</i>
<i>  A POSITION TO MAKE DEMANDS.</i>

454
00:30:05,270 --> 00:30:07,471
[ Nancy Whimpers ]

455
00:30:11,042 --> 00:30:13,543
- TED?
- NANCY.

456
00:30:13,612 --> 00:30:15,945
OH, TED, THANK GOD.

457
00:30:16,014 --> 00:30:18,548
ARE-- ARE YOU
AND LEIGH ALL RIGHT?

458
00:30:18,617 --> 00:30:22,185
YEAH. WE'RE A LITTLE GROUND UP,
BUT WE'RE, UM-- WE'RE ALIVE.

459
00:30:22,253 --> 00:30:25,888
JUST HANG IN THERE, SWEETIE.
EVERYTHING'S GONNA BE OKAY.

460
00:30:25,957 --> 00:30:27,890
TED, I LOVE YOU.

461
00:30:30,562 --> 00:30:33,630
I LOVE YOU TOO.
BOTH OF YOU.

462
00:30:33,699 --> 00:30:37,200
- MIDNIGHT.
- I'LL BE THERE.

463
00:30:39,738 --> 00:30:42,505
I GOT IT.

464
00:31:12,538 --> 00:31:14,471
<i>[ Bird Squawking ]</i>

465
00:31:14,540 --> 00:31:16,640
<i>[ Ted On Walkie-talkie ]</i>
<i>I MADE THE DELIVERY.</i>

466
00:31:16,708 --> 00:31:19,108
[ Sighs ]
ALL RIGHT.
IT'S BEEN OVER AN HOUR.

467
00:31:19,178 --> 00:31:22,278
I HAVEN'T SEEN ANYTHING YET
IN MY POSITION.
HOW ABOUT YOU, RAYMOND?

468
00:31:22,347 --> 00:31:24,547
<i>[ Ted ]</i>
<i>YEAH. DO YOU SEE ANYTHING?</i>
<i>HOW'S IT GOIN'?</i>

469
00:31:24,616 --> 00:31:26,849
NOTHIN' SO FAR.
[ Frank ]
WELL, KEEP YOUR HEAD UP.

470
00:31:26,918 --> 00:31:30,286
- JAROD.
- I DON'T LIKE THIS, SHERIFF.

471
00:31:30,354 --> 00:31:33,456
- HE SHOULD'VE SHOWN UP BY NOW.
-<i> [ Raymond ] JAROD,</i>
<i>  I THINK I GOT SOMETHING.</i>

472
00:31:33,525 --> 00:31:36,893
- [ Gunshot On Walkie-talkie ]
- DAMN! RAYMOND!
- RAYMOND, CAN YOU HEAR ME?

473
00:31:39,331 --> 00:31:41,264
WHAT THE HELL HAPPENED?

474
00:31:41,333 --> 00:31:43,800
I SAW THE GUY
COMING STRAIGHT AT ME.
[ Sighs ]

475
00:31:43,869 --> 00:31:47,037
HE WAS ON A MOTORCYCLE.
I THOUGHT I COULD STOP HIM.

476
00:31:47,105 --> 00:31:49,706
NEXT THING I KNEW I WAS DOWN.

477
00:31:49,774 --> 00:31:52,042
THE BULLET ENTERED
FROM BEHIND.
<i>[ Owl Hooting ]</i>

478
00:31:52,110 --> 00:31:54,077
HOW CAN THAT BE?

479
00:31:55,446 --> 00:31:57,446
THERE ARE TWO KIDNAPPERS.

480
00:32:01,420 --> 00:32:03,353
[ Elevator Bell Dings ]

481
00:32:03,422 --> 00:32:05,788
NEVER AGAIN. YOU HEAR ME?
DON'T EVEN ASK. NEVER AGAIN.

482
00:32:05,857 --> 00:32:08,458
CALM DOWN
AND CHECK YOUR PANTS.
[ Sighs ]

483
00:32:08,527 --> 00:32:12,095
NOW TELL ME WHAT YOU FOUND.
NOTHING. WELL, ALMOST NOTHING.

484
00:32:12,163 --> 00:32:14,564
[ Clears Throat ]
EXCUSE ME.

485
00:32:14,633 --> 00:32:18,168
I CROSS-REFERENCED EVERYTHING IN
RAINES'S FILES WITH EDNA'S NAME,
AND THE ONLY THING--

486
00:32:18,236 --> 00:32:20,736
THE ONLY THING
I CAME UP WITH...

487
00:32:20,805 --> 00:32:24,307
WAS SECTION "G,"
14, DASH, SIX...

488
00:32:24,376 --> 00:32:27,244
<i>IN A COMMUNIQUÉ INTERCEPTED</i>
<i>BY RAINES FROM EDNA TO YOU.</i>

489
00:32:28,746 --> 00:32:31,648
<i> WH-- WHAT?</i>

490
00:32:33,785 --> 00:32:35,985
SECTION "G."

491
00:32:36,054 --> 00:32:38,187
ROW 14, PLOT SIX.

492
00:32:38,257 --> 00:32:40,590
THAT'S MY MOTHER'S GRAVE.

493
00:32:41,660 --> 00:32:43,726
JAROD'S E-MAIL
SAID TO KEEP DIGGING.

494
00:32:43,795 --> 00:32:47,163
THE ANSWERS...
ARE BURIED OUT THERE.

495
00:32:49,967 --> 00:32:52,668
YOU DON'T THINK JAROD
WANTS YOU TO DIG HER UP?

496
00:32:55,073 --> 00:32:58,441
MISS PARKER,
IT'S YOUR MOTHER'S GRAVE.

497
00:33:00,879 --> 00:33:04,647
GET SHOVELS.
WE'VE GOT WORK TO DO.

498
00:33:07,452 --> 00:33:09,986
[ Sighs ]
<i>[ Ted's Voice ]</i>
<i>THEY'RE DEAD.</i>

499
00:33:10,055 --> 00:33:13,456
IF THE KIDNAPPERS
HAVEN'T KILLED THEM ALREADY,
THEY WILL NOW FOR SURE.

500
00:33:13,524 --> 00:33:15,458
[ Sighs ]

501
00:33:15,526 --> 00:33:16,993
WHAT ARE YOU DOIN'?

502
00:33:17,062 --> 00:33:19,896
I'M GONNA
WATCH THIS VIDEO AGAIN.
MAYBE I MISSED SOMETHING.

503
00:33:19,965 --> 00:33:23,633
CAN'T BELIEVE YOU DIDN'T
BRING ME HERE BEFORE NOW.

504
00:33:25,303 --> 00:33:29,005
[ Leigh ]
ARE YOU OKAY? IF YOU'RE JOKING
AROUND, THIS ISN'T FUNNY!

505
00:33:30,241 --> 00:33:33,509
WELL, NOT COMPLETE.
HA, HA, HA.

506
00:33:33,578 --> 00:33:36,913
<i>[ Young Jarod's Voice ]</i>
<i>I'VE STUDIED THE EVIDENCE</i>
<i>AND READ THE INTERVIEWS, BUT...</i>

507
00:33:36,981 --> 00:33:38,414
IT JUST DOESN'T MAKE SENSE.

508
00:33:38,483 --> 00:33:41,751
THE ANSWER'S
RIGHT IN FRONT OF YOU.
EVERYTHING YOU NEED IS THERE.

509
00:33:41,820 --> 00:33:43,586
BUT I CAN'T SEE IT.
<i>BUT SHE CAN.</i>

510
00:33:43,655 --> 00:33:45,688
SEE WHAT IT IS THAT SHE SEES.

511
00:33:45,757 --> 00:33:49,058
<i>LOOK, JAROD.</i>
<i> LOOK HARD.</i>

512
00:33:52,563 --> 00:33:54,263
DID YOU SEE THAT?

513
00:33:55,633 --> 00:33:57,667
WHAT?

514
00:34:01,239 --> 00:34:03,707
THAT.

515
00:34:08,980 --> 00:34:11,848
<i>THE ANSWER'S THERE.</i>
<i>IT WAS THERE THE WHOLE TIME.</i>

516
00:34:15,887 --> 00:34:18,688
SHE SEES HIM.

517
00:34:18,757 --> 00:34:21,891
<i> [ Frank ]</i>
<i> ADAMS? HE WAS</i>
<i> IN THE PARKING LOT?</i>

518
00:34:21,959 --> 00:34:23,893
<i>[ Ted ]</i>
<i>ADAMS? WHO'S ADAMS?</i>

519
00:34:23,962 --> 00:34:26,429
- MY DEPUTY.
- AND ONE OF THE KIDNAPPERS.

520
00:34:26,498 --> 00:34:29,098
- THEN WHO'S THE OTHER ONE?
- MY GUESS IS
HIS BROTHER KENT...

521
00:34:29,167 --> 00:34:30,733
FROM THE GAS STATION.

522
00:34:30,801 --> 00:34:33,769
SO THESE GUYS HAVE GONE
TO KILL MY FAMILY?
NOT IF WE GET TO THEM FIRST.

523
00:34:33,838 --> 00:34:36,806
WAIT A MINUTE.

524
00:34:36,875 --> 00:34:38,607
<i>LISTEN TO THIS.</i>
[ Ted's Voice ]
NANCY.

525
00:34:38,676 --> 00:34:42,078
- [ Nancy ]
OH, TED, THANK GOD.
-<i> ARE YOU AND LEIGH ALL RIGHT?</i>

526
00:34:42,146 --> 00:34:44,914
WE'RE A LITTLE GROUND UP,
BUT WE'RE, UM-- WE'RE ALIVE.

527
00:34:44,983 --> 00:34:48,151
WE'RE A LITTLE GROUND UP--
WE'RE A LITTLE GROUND UP--

528
00:34:48,220 --> 00:34:50,286
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.
"GROUND UP."

529
00:34:50,355 --> 00:34:52,655
ON THE VIDEO,
LEIGH KEPT REFERRING
TO AN OLD MILL.

530
00:34:52,724 --> 00:34:56,459
YEAH, NEAR MY FATHER-IN-LAW'S
RANCH. NANCY AND I USED TO
GO THERE ALL THE TIME.

531
00:34:56,528 --> 00:34:59,495
YOU WIFE WAS TRYING TO TELL YOU
WHERE SHE AND YOUR DAUGHTER
WERE BEING HELD.

532
00:34:59,564 --> 00:35:02,198
LET'S GO.

533
00:35:02,267 --> 00:35:04,968
LET'S JUST HOPE
THEY'RE STILL ALIVE.

534
00:35:13,678 --> 00:35:18,348
<i>[ Crickets Chirping ]</i>
<i>[ Owl Hooting ]</i>

535
00:35:26,124 --> 00:35:29,525
<i>[ Broots ] YOU'VE MADE ME DO</i>
<i>A LOT OF THINGS I DON'T</i>
<i>WANT TO DO, MISS PARKER,</i>

536
00:35:29,594 --> 00:35:32,462
BUT THIS HAS GOTTA BE
THE WORST.

537
00:35:32,530 --> 00:35:34,464
WHAT IF SOMEONE FINDS US?

538
00:35:34,532 --> 00:35:37,266
THEN YOU'LL JUST HAVE TO
HOLD THEM OFF
WHILE I GO FOR HELP.

539
00:35:37,335 --> 00:35:39,268
OH, GREAT.
THAT'S-- THAT'S LOVELY.

540
00:35:39,337 --> 00:35:41,337
ROW 14'S OVER HERE.

541
00:35:41,406 --> 00:35:43,906
<i>[ Thunder Rumbling ]</i>

542
00:35:47,679 --> 00:35:50,079
<i> [ Clank ]</i>
[ Broots Whispers ]
WHOA. SORRY.

543
00:35:52,450 --> 00:35:55,184
I FEEL LIKE I'M IN
A SCOOBY-DOO CARTOON.
<i>[ Owl Hoots ]</i>

544
00:35:55,253 --> 00:35:59,088
WAIT. WHAT WAS THAT?
SETTLE DOWN, SHAGGY.

545
00:35:59,157 --> 00:36:01,157
IT'S AN OWL.

546
00:36:07,432 --> 00:36:10,432
<i>[ Owl Hooting ]</i>

547
00:36:10,501 --> 00:36:13,002
THIS IS IT.

548
00:36:14,072 --> 00:36:17,340
<i>MISS PARKER,</i>
<i>THIS JUST ISN'T RIGHT.</i>

549
00:36:17,409 --> 00:36:20,009
ARE YOU SURE
YOU WANT TO DO THIS?

550
00:36:22,214 --> 00:36:24,481
JAROD'S DONE
A LOT OF TWISTED THINGS,

551
00:36:25,817 --> 00:36:28,817
BUT HE WOULD NEVER
LEAD ME HERE
JUST TO TORMENT ME.

552
00:36:28,886 --> 00:36:32,121
<i>[ Thunder Rumbling ]</i>

553
00:36:35,293 --> 00:36:37,292
NOW DIG.

554
00:37:02,153 --> 00:37:04,654
<i>[ Vehicle Approaching ]</i>

555
00:37:05,757 --> 00:37:08,357
<i> [ Vehicle Door Opens ]</i>

556
00:37:10,128 --> 00:37:12,395
WHERE THE HELL
HAVE YOU BEEN?
WRIGHT TIPPED OFF THE SHERIFF.

557
00:37:12,464 --> 00:37:15,498
- WE GOTTA GET OUT OF HERE.
- NO ONE FOLLOWED ME.

558
00:37:15,567 --> 00:37:18,401
THAT'S BECAUSE
I PUT A BULLET IN THE LEG
OF THE GUY WHO COULD'VE.

559
00:37:18,470 --> 00:37:20,403
WHAT ABOUT THEM?

560
00:37:26,778 --> 00:37:28,710
THIS WASN'T
PART OF OUR PLAN.

561
00:37:28,779 --> 00:37:30,880
<i>YEAH, WELL, PLANS CHANGE,</i>
<i>LITTLE BROTHER.</i>

562
00:37:30,948 --> 00:37:33,282
<i>THEY CAN IDENTIFY US.</i>

563
00:37:33,351 --> 00:37:35,618
[ Grunts ]

564
00:37:35,687 --> 00:37:37,086
<i> [ Grunts ]</i>

565
00:37:37,155 --> 00:37:39,888
LEIGH, NOW! RUN!

566
00:37:43,427 --> 00:37:45,428
<i> I'LL GET THE DAUGHTER.</i>
<i> YOU TAKE CARE OF HER.</i>

567
00:37:57,375 --> 00:37:59,142
DAMN, MOM. THAT HURT.

568
00:37:59,211 --> 00:38:01,644
IF THAT'S THE WAY
YOU'RE GONNA BE--

569
00:38:03,948 --> 00:38:06,315
<i> OH, I DON'T THINK SO.</i>

570
00:38:06,384 --> 00:38:08,151
[ Groans ]

571
00:38:09,987 --> 00:38:12,455
- NANCY.
- I'M FINE.

572
00:38:12,524 --> 00:38:15,157
<i>BUT LEIGH-- SHE RAN OUT,</i>
<i>AND THE DEPUTY WENT AFTER HER.</i>

573
00:38:16,560 --> 00:38:18,160
[ Panting ]

574
00:38:18,229 --> 00:38:20,096
[ Panting, Whimpers ]

575
00:38:20,165 --> 00:38:22,298
[ Panting ]

576
00:38:29,440 --> 00:38:31,407
<i>[ Adams ]</i>
<i>YOU CAN'T GET AWAY.</i>

577
00:38:42,153 --> 00:38:46,089
[ Groans ]
GET AWAY FROM ME!

578
00:38:46,157 --> 00:38:49,191
DON'T WORK THAT WAY.

579
00:38:49,260 --> 00:38:52,428
IT'S NOTHING PERSONAL.
YOU UNDERSTAND.
PLEASE. I WANT TO GO HOME.

580
00:38:52,496 --> 00:38:55,864
JUST BUSINESS.
PLEASE. I WANT TO GO HOME.

581
00:38:55,933 --> 00:38:59,468
- THE ONLY PLACE YOU'RE GOING
IS IN KOOMER'S CREEK!
- NO! [ Screams ]

582
00:38:59,537 --> 00:39:02,138
STOP SCREAMIN'.
NO ONE CAN HEAR YOU
SCREAM OUT HERE.

583
00:39:02,206 --> 00:39:03,673
I CAN.

584
00:39:08,012 --> 00:39:09,945
COME HERE!

585
00:39:13,517 --> 00:39:15,184
[ Groans ]

586
00:39:42,447 --> 00:39:44,380
ARE YOU OKAY?
ARE YOU OKAY?
[ Sobbing ]

587
00:39:44,449 --> 00:39:47,050
IT'S OKAY.
[ Whispers ] IT'S FINE.
IT'S FINE. IT'S FINE.

588
00:39:47,118 --> 00:39:49,051
<i> [ Nancy ]</i>
<i> LEIGH.</i>
GO. GO.

589
00:39:50,522 --> 00:39:52,455
LEIGH.
LEIGH.

590
00:39:52,524 --> 00:39:55,091
BABY. OH.

591
00:40:01,199 --> 00:40:03,199
I DON'T KNOW HOW TO
THANK YOU, JAROD.

592
00:40:03,268 --> 00:40:05,534
JUST TAKE CARE OF THEM.

593
00:40:07,338 --> 00:40:09,805
I WILL.

594
00:40:09,874 --> 00:40:12,008
YOU READY TO GO?
LET'S GO HOME.

595
00:40:22,220 --> 00:40:24,887
<i>[ Thunder Rumbling ]</i>

596
00:40:28,559 --> 00:40:30,559
WELL, THIS IS IT.

597
00:40:32,030 --> 00:40:35,097
<i> MISS PARKER, ARE YOU SURE</i>
<i> YOU WANT TO DO THIS?</i>

598
00:40:36,167 --> 00:40:38,100
AH.
<i> HUH?</i>

599
00:40:38,169 --> 00:40:40,169
[ Sighs ]

600
00:40:41,272 --> 00:40:43,472
OPEN IT.
MISS PARKER--

601
00:40:43,541 --> 00:40:47,076
[ Sighs ]
WHY DON'T WE JUST
GET THE HELL OUT OF HERE...

602
00:40:47,144 --> 00:40:49,378
AND LET HER REST IN PEACE?
[ Sighs ]

603
00:40:50,448 --> 00:40:54,283
<i> I</i> WANT TO REST IN PEACE.

604
00:40:54,352 --> 00:40:56,885
<i> NOW OPEN IT.</i>

605
00:41:03,394 --> 00:41:05,394
ARE YOU SURE?

606
00:41:10,034 --> 00:41:12,034
GO AHEAD.

607
00:41:26,918 --> 00:41:28,917
[ Grunts ]

608
00:41:32,824 --> 00:41:34,823
OH, MY GOD.

609
00:41:34,892 --> 00:41:37,860
WHAT?
<i> MISS PARKER,</i>
<i> YOUR MOTHER--</i>

610
00:41:40,098 --> 00:41:42,865
SHE'S NOT IN HERE.

611
00:42:06,624 --> 00:42:08,724
THEN WHERE THE HELL IS SHE?

612
00:42:25,442 --> 00:42:28,677
[ Miss Parker ]
JAROD, I'M ONLY
GOING TO ASK YOU THIS ONCE.

613
00:42:28,746 --> 00:42:31,079
HOW DID YOU KNOW
SHE WOULDN'T BE THERE?

614
00:42:31,148 --> 00:42:33,382
I DIDN'T.
THEN WHO?

615
00:42:33,450 --> 00:42:36,185
EDNA DID.
SHE KNEW ALL THE SECRETS.

616
00:42:36,254 --> 00:42:38,654
ESPECIALLY ABOUT
THE MIRAGE PROJECT.

617
00:42:38,722 --> 00:42:41,123
UNFORTUNATELY,
SHE TOOK THEM TO HER GRAVE.

618
00:42:41,191 --> 00:42:44,593
WELL, I AM SORRY FOR YOU.
EDNA WAS SOMEONE
YOU COULD'VE TRUSTED.

619
00:42:44,662 --> 00:42:47,429
UNLIKE THE CENTRE.

620
00:42:47,498 --> 00:42:49,498
OR MY FAMILY.

621
00:42:49,567 --> 00:42:51,901
YOU WERE RIGHT IN PUTTING
YOUR TRUST IN YOUR MOTHER.

622
00:42:51,970 --> 00:42:53,902
SHE KNEW THE IMPORTANCE
OF FAMILY.

623
00:42:53,971 --> 00:42:55,905
OF HELPING PEOPLE.

624
00:42:55,974 --> 00:42:58,541
IF SHE KEPT
ANY SECRETS FROM YOU,
IT WAS TO PROTECT YOU.

625
00:42:58,609 --> 00:43:01,443
PROTECT ME FROM WHAT?

626
00:43:01,512 --> 00:43:02,912
THE TRUTH.

627
00:43:02,980 --> 00:43:05,213
KEEP SEARCHING, MISS PARKER.

628
00:43:05,282 --> 00:43:09,351
BUT REMEMBER.
YOU CAN'T BELIEVE
EVERYTHING YOU SEE.

629
00:43:11,522 --> 00:43:14,256
AFTER ALL,
LIFE IS A MIRAGE.

630
00:43:14,325 --> 00:43:16,692
SOMETIMES THE THINGS
THAT SCARE YOU THE MOST...

631
00:43:16,761 --> 00:43:19,028
CAN BE THE THINGS
THAT SAVE YOUR LIFE.

632
00:43:23,334 --> 00:43:25,334
[ Beeps ]

